Just in time for the 4th of July, the Major Issues crew takes a hard look at Truth: Red, White & Black, Marvel’s powerful reimagining of the super-soldier origin. We break down the story of Isaiah Bradley, the forgotten Black Captain America, and how the series confronts racism, patriotism, and the darker side of American history. What does this bold comic say about legacy and who gets to be a hero? Tune in for a timely and thought-provoking discussion.

Please leave us a review on [ITunes](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by ComicBook Clique, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

